ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: First Latency to Peek Over Shoulder- Bow
First Latency to Turn Around- Bow

Notes: 0 = Turning around to peek, 1 = Peeking over the shoulder, 2 = No attempt to peek

ElementDescription: Total Number of Times Peeked- Bow
Notes: Number of times (once per second for 3 minute delay)

ElementDescription: How does the participant unwrap gift-Bow
Notes: 0 = Rips it open, 1 = Begins neatly then rips, 2 - Neatly carefully unwraps

ElementDescription: First Latency to Peek Over Shoulder-Wrap
First Latency to Turn Around- Wrap

Notes: 0 = Turning around to peek, 1 = Peeking over the shoulder, 2 = No attempt to peek
Number of times (once per second for 1 minute delay)

ElementDescription: How does the participant unwrap gift-Wrap
Notes: 0 = Rips it open, 1 = Begins neatly then rips, 2 - Neatly carefully unwraps
